<br>
Character selection and creation is VERY nice. I like being able to walk around the starting room and see all my characters standing there. Neato.<br>
<br>
The actual in game menus look nice, but man what a pain in the ass. Mouse response was slow as hell for me, not to mention walking around in general being slow. The fading menus were neat at first, but started pissing me off after a few minutes (the amount of time it took me to figure out how to turn it off). I like having 8 slots per page on the spellbook, but don't like having to learn new icons. I spent literally an hour just trying to find a background color for the chat window that allowed me to actually read what was being said... and failed.... which means I would have to completely rework my current color scheme. The textured background they give you is too dark to actually read text against, no matter what tint color you give it, which means that chat windows might have to be solid colors (at least for me, heh).<br>
<br>
And then I started a wood elf in gfay and .. well... they completely screwed up the newbie zone. It's just not possible to level there without twinking now. The normal newbie area is filled with monsters for the new armor quests, all of which are yellow or red to level 1. After 15 minutes, I finally found an even con decaying skeleton, and as soon as I attacked it, one of the new (red-con) mini-treant monsters KSed it from me.<br>
<br>
My verdict: I really hope they leave an option to use the current interface, because I don't like this one.  It would take me weeks to get used to it.  Heh, I complain a lot... <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
